<para>
  <classname>QuadSplit</classname> is a <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-Rationalizer"/> applied by the <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-Rationalize"/> &skel; <link
  linkend="RegisteredClass-SkeletonModifier">modifier</link>.  As
  shown in <xref linkend="Figure-splitwide"/> it splits quadrilateral
  &elems; into two triangular &elems;, if the quadrilateral has an
  interior angle greater than <varname>angle</varname>.  Unlike other
  rationalizers, <classname>QuadSplit</classname> doesn't affect its
  neighboring elements.
</para>

<figure id="Figure-splitwide">
  <title>Applying QuadSplit</title>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata fileref="FIGURES/ration/splitwide.png"
                 contentwidth="414px" format="PNG"/>
    </imageobject>
    <caption>
      <simpara>
        The highlighted quadrilateral &elem; in (a) is split into two
        triangles in (b).
      </simpara>
    </caption>
  </mediaobject>
</figure>


